DUTSE – Jigawa State Police Commissioner, Usman Sule Gwamna, has pledged to close rank with the police in ensuring that the state is violence-free. Gwanma disclosed this while receiving Speaker of the state House of Assembly, Idris Garba Jahun, a courtesy visit in Dutse. Addressing a press conference shortly after the visit, Jahun noted that they have discussed crucial matters relating to with the security, among other vital issues. “My visit on Jigawa State Police Commissioner wasn’t unusual, but officials, as we discussed matters of common interest,” said the speaker. Earlier in his response, Gwamna commended the Speaker for the visit and assured of the Police cooperation with government organs on matters of collective responsibility. He stressed the need for community policing through advocacy for the down trodden.